Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Tear the @Ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks.

Pop the ciabatta chunks onto a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and toss to coat well.

When the oven is hot, bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the oven and transfer to a #plate{}.

Meanwhile, chop the @Sweet Potato{2}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large baking tray. Drizzle with oil and season, then sprinkle over the @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While everything cooks, halve the @Bell Pepper{1}(halved, seeds and core removed) and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Once the croutons are done, set aside for now. Pop the sliced pepper onto the (now empty) baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast the pepper on the middle shelf until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Dressing and Assembly ==

Add the @Ranch Dressing{60%grams} to a large #bowl{}.

Cut the @Medium Tomato{1}(cut into 1cm chunks) into 1cm chunks and add to the dressing.

Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a #board{} in one piece, then thinly slice widthways. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything's ready, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%grams}, Cajun sweet potato, roasted pepper, @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams} and croutons to the bowl of tomatoes and dressing. Gently toss to combine.

Share your warm sweet potato salad between your #bowls{}, then fan out the avocado in the centre of your salad.

Finish by crumbling over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{100%grams} and sprinkling with the @Pumpkin Seeds{15%grams}. Enjoy!